</div></figure>


<div style="height:21px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="ozyegin-university-faculty-of-engineering">Ozyegin University Faculty of Engineering</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Özyeğin University Faculty of Engineering is known for its interdisciplinary approach and applied education model. The Civil Engineering department within the faculty offers education not only at undergraduate but also at master&#8217;s and doctoral level, opening the door to a research-based career. If you want to get more information about <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/ozyegin-muhendislik-fakultesi/" data-type="post" data-id="3048">Özyeğin University Faculty of Engineering</a>, you can take a detailed look.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-does-civil-engineering-tuition-cost-2025-2026">How Much Does Civil Engineering Tuition Cost? 2025-2026</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many private universities in Turkey update their tuition fees every year. Özyeğin University has set the <strong>annual tuition fee for the <strong>Faculty of Engineering</strong> at 22,000 USD</strong> as of 2026. This fee is the standard list for non-scholarship (i.e. 0% scholarship) students.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Below, you can see the current fee and scholarship status of Özyeğin University Faculty of Engineering for 2025-2026 by department:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Department</th>
<th>Cost of Study (USD/Year)</th>
<th>Language of Study</th>
<th>Scholarship Opportunities</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Civil Engineering</strong></td>
<td>$22,000</td>
<td>English</td>
<td>Full / 50% / Paid</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These fees are annual and do not remain fixed throughout the study period; the university may update them by 10-20% each year. However, the scholarship rate indicated at the time of admission remains fixed for the entire duration of the student&#8217;s studies.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-do-you-pay-with-scholarships">How much do you pay with scholarships?</h4>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Full Scholarship</strong>: $0 (Free)</li>



<li><strong>50% Scholarship</strong>: $11,000</li>



<li><strong>Paid</strong> (without scholarship): $22,000</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:24px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-civil-engineering-what-is-its-purpose">What is Civil Engineering, What is its Purpose?</h2>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="this-occupation-is-not-limited-to-buildings">This Occupation is Not Limited to Buildings</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">While only buildings come to mind when we think of civil engineering, this field is actually divided into many sub-disciplines such as water structures, transportation systems, environmental engineering and earth sciences. Therefore, this program provides not only engineering but also a broad vision of design, environmental awareness and sustainability.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="a-globally-valid-occupation">A Globally Valid Occupation</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Civil engineering is a profession that is in global demand and recognized in <strong>every country</strong>. Özyeğin University aims to provide its students with the technical equipment and cultural understanding to work in different geographies. When you graduate, you can find a job not only in Turkey but also in many regions from Europe to the Gulf countries.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:24px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-courses-will-you-take-in-the-civil-engineering-program">What Courses Will You Take in the Civil Engineering Program?</h2>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="basic-courses-and-technical-competencies">Basic Courses and Technical Competencies</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Basic Lessons Learned in the Early Years:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Mathematics (Calculus I-II)</li>



<li>Physics (Mechanics, Electricity &amp; Magnetism)</li>



<li>Engineering Drawing and Technical Drawing</li>



<li>Computer Aided Design (CAD)</li>



<li>Materials Science</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Field Courses Taken in Upper Grades:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Structure Statics and Strength</li>



<li>Geotechnical Engineering</li>



<li>Hydraulics and Water Resources</li>



<li>Building Materials</li>



<li>Transport Engineering</li>



<li>Construction Management and Project Planning</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>English Education Advantage:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Ease of access to international resources</li>



<li>Knowledge of global engineering terminology</li>



<li>Advantage in international graduate applications</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="specialization-areas-sustainability-and-digitalization">Specialization Areas: Sustainability and Digitalization</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In the final years of the program, students have the opportunity to specialize according to their interests. Two main areas of specialization are offered:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Climate Change and Sustainability</strong></li>



<li><strong>Digitalization and Artificial Intelligence in Civil Engineering</strong></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This way, competencies are gained to produce solutions not only for today&#8217;s problems but also for the problems of the future.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="sample-table-of-compulsory-and-elective-courses">Sample Table of Compulsory and Elective Courses</h4>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Course Category</th>
<th>Course Examples</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
