<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some sources suggest a total amount of <strong>$5,000 to $8,000</strong> for a year, but this can vary based on the city (major cities like Istanbul are more expensive) and your university. It is highly recommended that your bank statements show consistent funds over a period of at least the last three months to avoid suspicion of a sudden large deposit. If you have a scholarship, you will need to provide proof of the scholarship award as your financial evidence.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-get-a-student-visa">How to Get a Student Visa</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey student visa applications are usually submitted through the Consulate or Embassy of the Republic of Turkey in the student&#8217;s country of citizenship. The process involves several steps and applications are usually finalized within 2 to 8 weeks. This time varies depending on the consulate density and the completeness of the applicant&#8217;s documents. You can check your country-specific processes on the <a href="https://www.mfa.gov.tr/default.tr.mfa" target="_blank" rel="noopener">T.C. Ministry of Foreign Affairs&#8217; Visa General Information</a> page.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-many-days-does-it-take-to-issue-a-student-visa">How Many Days Does It Take to Issue a Student Visa?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The length of the visa application process varies depending on the country of application, the intensity of the consulate and the completeness of the documents.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="expected-periods-in-the-application-process">Expected Periods in the Application Process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applications usually take between 2 and 8 weeks. During peak periods (e.g. summer months or university enrollment period) this period may be longer. Therefore, if possible, it is best to submit your application at least 2 months before your planned training start date.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="residence-permit-for-foreign-students">Residence Permit for Foreign Students</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This visa is required for entry into Turkey, but for longer stays a student residence permit is also required.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="procedures-after-entry-to-turkey-with-a-student-visa">Procedures After Entry to Turkey with a Student Visa</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Once you have received your visa, you can enter Turkey. When you enter with this visa at the airport, you should go to your university in Turkey and apply for a student residence permit.</p>



