<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-the-purpose-of-the-department-of-artificial-intelligence-and-data-engineering">What is the purpose of the Department of Artificial Intelligence and Data Engineering?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The main objective of this department is to train engineers who can develop artificial intelligence technologies and produce meaningful results through data analytics. The program provides students with basic engineering skills such as analytical thinking, problem solving and algorithm development, while encouraging them to develop innovative projects. It is an ideal choice for students who want to explore how artificial intelligence can be used in sectors such as healthcare, finance and automotive.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Another important goal of the program is to provide English language education so that students can compete in the international arena. In this way, graduates can become an indispensable part of teams developing artificial intelligence solutions not only in Turkey but also on a global scale.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="artificial-intelligence-and-data-engineering-education">Artificial Intelligence and Data Engineering Education</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Department of Artificial Intelligence and Data Engineering at Ozyegin University offers its students a contemporary and innovative education program. The department offers a four-year program in English. The academic staff consists of faculty members who are experts in artificial intelligence, machine learning and big data. In this way, students learn about the latest technologies and applications and have the opportunity to solve real-world problems.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Before you start your education, you can also check our <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/ozyegin-muhendislik-fakultesi/" data-type="post" data-id="3048">Özyeğin University Faculty of Engineering</a> page for other departments and details of Özyeğin University Faculty of Engineering.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="courses-and-curriculum">Courses and Curriculum</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The curriculum of the program consists of courses that form the cornerstones of artificial intelligence and data engineering. While algorithms, programming languages and basic engineering courses are taught in the first years, advanced artificial intelligence courses such as deep learning, natural language processing and reinforcement learning are introduced in the following years. Students develop applications with programming languages such as Python, C++ and Java, and carry out data science projects. They also gain advantage after graduation by gaining sector experience through internships and graduation projects.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="internship-and-sector-collaborations">Internship and Sector Collaborations</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Özyeğin University&#8217;s strong connections with industry give students experience in real-world projects. In this way, they have the chance to develop artificial intelligence solutions and specialize in data analysis before graduation. Thanks to the university&#8217;s industry collaborations, students also have an advantage in employment after graduation.</p>


<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:24px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="artificial-intelligence-and-data-engineering-base-points-and-quotas">Artificial Intelligence and Data Engineering Base Points and Quotas</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the most important criteria used for admission to universities in Turkey is the score and ranking obtained from the YKS exam. Özyeğin University Department of Artificial Intelligence and Data Engineering has a total of 29 openings for the 2025-2026 academic year. These quotas accept students in two main scholarship categories; 4 full scholarships and 25 50% scholarships.</p>



