UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Short Term Study Visa in Turkey: 2025 Guide","description":"Everything you need to know about short term study visas in Turkey is here! Read our 2025 guide and get one step closer to your education dreams.","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Short Term Study Visa in Turkey: 2025 Guide","ogDescription":"Everything you need to know about short term study visas in Turkey is here! Read our 2025 guide and get one step closer to your education dreams.","ogImage":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/short-term-education-visa-in-turkiye-2025-guide-1024x772.webp","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Short Term Study Visa in Turkey: 2025 Guide","twitterDescription":"Everything you need to know about short term study visas in Turkey is here! Read our 2025 guide and get one step closer to your education dreams.","canonicalPath":"/en/short-term-study-visa/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/kisa-donem-egitim-vizesi/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/short-term-study-visa/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/short-term-education-visa-in-turkiye-2025-guide.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/short-term-education-visa-in-turkiye-2025-guide.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"Student preparing documents for short-term education visa in Turkey 2025","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/short-term-study-visa/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/short-term-study-visa/","name":"Short Term Study Visa in Turkey: 2025 Guide","datePublished":"2025-08-27T13:00:47+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:44:45+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/short-term-education-visa-in-turkiye-2025-guide.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Short Term Study Visa in Turkey: 2025 Guide","keywords":"Short Term Study","datePublished":"2025-08-27T13:00:47+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:44:45+03:00","articleSection":"Visa and Immigration","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Everything you need to know about short term study visas in Turkey is here! Read our 2025 guide and get one step closer to your education dreams.","name":"Short Term Study Visa in Turkey: 2025 Guide","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/short-term-study-visa/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/short-term-study-visa/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/short-term-education-visa-in-turkiye-2025-guide.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/short-term-study-visa/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This guide for international students seeking a short term study visa in Turkey will help you understand the seemingly complicated details of the process. When I came to Turkey for a short term study program myself, I realized that this process is more complicated than I thought. Documents, appointments, which type of visa, etc. really confuse people. Fortunately, I am now explaining this process for you piece by piece.</p>


<h2 id="kisa-donem-egitim-visa-nedir-ve-kimler-icin-uygundur" class="wp-block-heading">What Is A Short Term Study Visa And Who Is It Suitable For?</h2>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A short term study visa is an official permit for foreign students who wish to come to Turkey for less than 90 days for education, courses or seminars. This visa is especially ideal for summer school, language courses or short term academic programs.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are going on a long-term study program (over 90 days), you will need to apply for a student residence permit. However, a short term study visa offers a practical and fast solution for short term study plans.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="types-of-short-term-study-visas-in-turkey">Types of Short Term Study Visas in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers a single type of visa for short term study visa applications, usually called a &#8220;short term study visa&#8221;. However, this visa can be divided into several subcategories depending on the purpose of your visa:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Language Courses: Courses you will attend for Turkish or foreign language training.</li>



<li>Summer Schools: Short term summer programs organized by universities or private schools.</li>



<li>Academic Seminar or Workshop: For those who want to participate in activities such as research projects, summer school, etc.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://www.mfa.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The official website of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Turkey</a> provides detailed information on this type of visa.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="visa-application-process-and-required-documents">Visa Application Process and Required Documents</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The first step in applying for a short term study visa is to make an appointment at a Turkish foreign representative office (consulate or embassy). At this stage, using the online application system will make your job easier.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">I had a nightmare when I was applying because I forgot my documents on the way to the appointment; let me tell you, take the documents in full! Here are the documents usually required:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Current passport (valid for at least 6 months from travel)</li>



<li>Application form (must be filled in online and printed out)</li>



<li>Acceptance letter or course/seminar invitation</li>



<li>Travel health insurance</li>



<li>Flight and accommodation reservations</li>



<li>Visa fee payment receipt</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The result of your application is usually announced within 1-2 weeks. This period can sometimes be extended, so it is important to submit your application as early as possible.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="visa-renewal-and-extension-procedures">Visa Renewal and Extension Procedures</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A short term study visa in Turkey is usually issued for no more than 90 days. However, some students may wish to renew or extend their visa if their program extends or if they pursue additional study opportunities.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When I was going through this process, at first I thought I had to apply for a visa again for the extension process; it turned out that I had to apply for a student residence permit! So: After arriving in Turkey, you need to apply to the Immigration Administration for a short term residence permit before your visa expires.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can access the current application form on the official page of the Immigration Authority. The application usually requires the following:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Passport and visa photocopies</li>



<li>Student certificate from the educational institution you are enrolled in</li>



<li>Housing information (lease or dormitory certificate)</li>



<li>Health insurance</li>



<li>Biometric photo</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">After you make your application, you go to the Migration Management with your documents on the appointment day and complete the procedures. The result of your application is usually announced within a few weeks.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="study-experience-in-turkey-practical-information">Study Experience in Turkey: Practical Information</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Being a student in Turkey is not just about studying; it is also a cultural experience. When I first arrived, I discovered many new things, from learning how to bargain in the markets to street food. Especially for short term students, the best way to make the most of this experience is to follow both the opportunities offered by the school and the social events in the city.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In big cities like Istanbul, Ankara and Izmir, there are various social clubs, sports activities and cultural events for short term students. Language courses or summer schools usually organize city tours or cultural excursions on weekends. Don&#8217;t miss it!</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Transportation in Turkey is also very affordable. Public transportation discounts are available for students. It is both economical and practical to use buses, subways and trams with city cards such as Istanbulkart or Kentkart.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Also pay attention to the internet connection; a good connection is essential for studies and staying in touch with family. You can get short term student lines from Turkish operators.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="result">Result</h2>


<p>Getting a short term study visa in Turkey is not as complicated as you think; you can achieve your dream of studying by taking the right steps. Visit <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">RoadToStudy</a></p>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">for more information and professional support and get one step closer to your dream education!</p>



